-- Japan's Shiozaki says absolutely no intention to put off GPIF reform
-- By Takaya Yamaguchi
-- Thu Sep 25, 2014 11:23PM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, Sept 26 (Reuters) - Japan's welfare minister said on Friday that he has absolutely no intention to put off reforms for the country's giant pension fund.

Shiozaki was appointed this month to head the ministry that oversees the $1.26 trillion Government Pension Investment Fund (GPIF).